cs.SD, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on audio classification and learning feature representations for audio data. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper also uses visual data (RGB video) to train the audio models and aligns the visual and acoustic images in space and time. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep learning models and teacher-student learning to train the audio models. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with both audio and visual data modalities and their fusion for better feature representations. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): Although not as likely as the previous categories, the paper does mention classification and retrieval tasks in the context of audio data.
